216
0:10:3,000 --> 0:10:33,000
Ashraf Ghani: What scares me most is -- is you,

217
0:10:33,000 --> 0:10:35,000
lack of your engagement.

218
0:10:36,000 --> 0:10:4,000
(Laughter)

219
0:10:4,000 --> 0:10:43,000
You asked me. You know I always give the unconventional answer.

220
0:10:43,000 --> 0:10:45,000
No. But seriously,

221
0:10:45,000 --> 0:10:47,000
the issue of Afghanistan

222
0:10:47,000 --> 0:10:49,000
first has to be seen as,

223
0:10:49,000 --> 0:10:52,000
at least, a 10- to 20-year perspective.

224
0:10:53,000 --> 0:10:55,000
Today the world of globalization

225
0:10:55,000 --> 0:10:57,000
is on speed.

226
0:10:57,000 --> 0:10:59,000
Time has been compressed.

227
0:10:59,000 --> 0:11:02,000
And space does not exist for most people.

228
0:11:02,000 --> 0:11:04,000
But in my world --

229
0:11:04,000 --> 0:11:07,000
you know, when I went back to Afghanistan after 23 years,

230
0:11:07,000 --> 0:11:09,000
space had expanded.

231
0:11:09,000 --> 0:11:12,000
Every conceivable form of infrastructure had broken down.

232
0:11:12,000 --> 0:11:14,000
I rode -- traveled --

233
0:11:14,000 --> 0:11:17,000
travel between two cities that used to take three hours

234
0:11:17,000 --> 0:11:19,000
now took 12.

235
0:11:19,000 --> 0:11:22,000
So the first is when the scale is that,

236
0:11:22,000 --> 0:11:24,000
we need to recognize

237
0:11:24,000 --> 0:11:27,000
that just the simple things that are infrastructure --

238
0:11:27,000 --> 0:11:29,000
it takes six years to deliver infrastructure.

239
0:11:29,000 --> 0:11:31,000
In our world.

240
0:11:31,000 --> 0:11:34,000
Any meaningful sort of thing.

241
0:11:34,000 --> 0:11:37,000
But the modality of attention,

242
0:11:37,000 --> 0:11:4,000
or what is happening today, what's happening tomorrow.

243
0:11:4,000 --> 0:11:42,000
Second is,

244
0:11:42,000 --> 0:11:45,000
when a country has been subjected

245
0:11:45,000 --> 0:11:48,000
to one of the most immense, brutal forms of exercise of power --

246
0:11:48,000 --> 0:11:5,000
we had the Red Army

247
0:11:5,000 --> 0:11:52,000
for 10 continuous years,

248
0:11:52,000 --> 0:11:55,000
110,000 strong,

249
0:11:55,000 --> 0:11:58,000
literally terrorizing.

250
0:11:58,000 --> 0:12:,000
The sky:

251
0:12:,000 --> 0:12:03,000
every Afghan

252
0:12:03,000 --> 0:12:06,000
sees the sky as a source of fear.

253
0:12:07,000 --> 0:12:09,000
We were bombed

254
0:12:09,000 --> 0:12:12,000
practically out of existence.

255
0:12:14,000 --> 0:12:17,000
Then, tens of thousands of people were trained in terrorism --

256
0:12:19,000 --> 0:12:21,000
from all sides.

257
0:12:21,000 --> 0:12:23,000
The United States, Great Britain, joined for instance,

258
0:12:23,000 --> 0:12:25,000
Egyptian intelligence service

259
0:12:25,000 --> 0:12:27,000
to train thousands of people

260
0:12:27,000 --> 0:12:29,000
in resistance and urban terrorism.

261
0:12:31,000 --> 0:12:33,000
How to turn a bicycle

262
0:12:33,000 --> 0:12:36,000
into an instrument of terror.

263
0:12:36,000 --> 0:12:39,000
How to turn a donkey, a carthorse, anything.

264
0:12:39,000 --> 0:12:41,000
And the Russians, equally.

265
0:12:41,000 --> 0:12:43,000
So, when violence erupts

266
0:12:43,000 --> 0:12:45,000
in a country like Afghanistan,

267
0:12:45,000 --> 0:12:47,000
it's because of that legacy.

268
0:12:47,000 --> 0:12:49,000
But we have to understand

269
0:12:49,000 --> 0:12:51,000
that we've been incredibly lucky.

270
0:12:51,000 --> 0:12:54,000
I mean, I really can't believe how lucky I am here,

271
0:12:54,000 --> 0:12:57,000
standing in front of you, speaking.

272
0:12:57,000 --> 0:13:,000
When I joined as finance minister,

273
0:13:01,000 --> 0:13:04,000
I thought that the chances of my living more than three years

274
0:13:04,000 --> 0:13:07,000
would not be more than five percent.

275
0:13:08,000 --> 0:13:11,000
Those were the risks. They were worth it.

276
0:13:11,000 --> 0:13:13,000
I think we can make it,

277
0:13:13,000 --> 0:13:15,000
and the reason we can make it

278
0:13:15,000 --> 0:13:17,000
is because of the people.

279
0:13:17,000 --> 0:13:2,000
You see, because, I mean -- I give you one statistic.

280
0:13:2,000 --> 0:13:22,000
91 percent of the men in Afghanistan,

